OL,3,CCalls for more financial support over
OL,4,Chigh gluten-free food prices
OL,6,FShe explains: "The subsidy is provided
OL,7,Fby way of vouchers that can be
OL,8,Fredeemed at multiple supermarkets
OL,9,Facross the Island and equate to #728
OL,10,Fper annum (#56 every four weeks).
OL,12,F"The relative high cost of gluten-free
OL,13,Ffood has reduced since the scheme was
OL,14,Ffirst introduced in the 1990s, with
OL,15,Fgluten-free foods also now being far
OL,16,Fmore widely available.
