OL,3,CCalls for more financial support over
OL,4,Chigh gluten-free food prices
OL,6,F"The Government completed a periodic
OL,7,Freview of price comparisons of gluten-
OL,8,Ffree products earlier this year to
OL,9,Fensure that the subsidy is sufficient
OL,10,Fconsidering current prices."
OL,12,FKaren believes the government could go
OL,13,Ffurther, explaining: "What (the
OL,14,Fgovernment) need to remember is this
OL,15,Fis an illness. It's not somebody
OL,16,Fsomeone saying "Do you know what? I
OL,17,Ffancy gluten-free food." I don't fancy
OL,18,Fgluten-free food. Believe me.
OL,20,F"I have to eat gluten-free food. I
OL,21,Fhave no choice."
